<br>
In looking at the map of the Twilight Sea on eqatlas.com, there does not seem to be either a wizard or a druid portal location mentioned.  I assume that this is simply an oversight since I have confirmed that both druids and wizards can port into the TS.  With this being he case, which class would be preferable to use for the port?  Is one of the port locations significantly closer to Katta or in a safer location to zone in?<br>
<br>
After the port, will an invisibility spell be advisable?  I assume that it would be, but don't really know about mob aggro in the TS or if many mobs can see through invis.  I also assume that swimming will be necessary for the quick journey to the city entrance.  In terms of safety, should I avoid land altogether (e.g. swim around any islands) or take the closest, straightest path?<br>
<br>
In terms of the Katta inhabitants themselves, I have also read up on faction-related issues.  I assume from what I've read that an agnostic gnome mage should be accepted in the city, but if anyone has knowledge to counter this, it would be appreciated.  I will have &quot;see invisible&quot; up to help avoid the assassins in the city.  Does anyone know if these assassins can also see invisible as well as be invisible?<br>
<br>
